title.title: 16:55 hours - Incidents on London transport network

texts: Incidents at Warren St, Oval and Shepherd's Bush (Hammersmith & City) stations this afternoon have resulted in service suspension and disruption to parts of the London Underground network. These three stations remain closed.
We are working hard to restore services as quickly as possible.
Services are currently operating as follows and include service suspensions that were already in effect following incidents on 7 July 2005.
Bakerloo - suspended between Paddington to Piccadilly Circus
District - suspended between Edgware Road and High Street Kensington
Metropolitan - suspended between Baker Street to Aldgate
Northern - operating between Morden to Stockwell and Kennington to Edgware via Bank only
Piccadilly - operating between Cockfosters and Arnos Grove only
Victoria - operating between Walthamstow to Highbury & Islington and between Victoria to Brixton
